headlines.description: — Beginning a season of high expectations, the Atlanta Hawks showed they're far more than Trae Young.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young, Hawks open season with 113-87 rout of Mavericks

headlines.description: — Only one thing went wrong for the Miami Heat on Thursday night. Udonis Haslem voted no.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro scores 27 points, Heat rout Bucks 137-95 in opener

events.name: LA Clippers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry raised his arms, waved to acknowledge the adoring fans as shot after shot dropped through the net and screamed in celebration — no trash about it.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 45, Warriors hold off Clippers 115-113
